$\answer{-\alpha-\beta \text{ is a root of the equation given by} -\sqrt[3]{q+\sqrt{q^2-p^3}}-\sqrt[3]{q-\sqrt{q^2-p^3}}.}\textbf{A1}$

- 
  - Substituting $s=-3p$ and $t=2q$ we have the equation

    $$
    \begin{align*}
        x^3 - 3p+ 2q &= 0\\
    \end{align*}
    $$

    and according to part (b) (iv) we have the root

    $$
    \begin{align*} 
        -\sqrt[3]{q+\sqrt{q^2-p^3}}&-\sqrt[3]{q-\sqrt{q^2-p^3}}\\
    \end{align*}
    $$

    Reflecting on the desired result, we can rewrite each term by factorising with $-1$

    $$
    \begin{align*}
        = \sqrt[3]{-(q+\sqrt{q^2-p^3})}&+\sqrt[3]{-(q-\sqrt{q^2-p^3})}\\
        = \sqrt[3]{-q-\sqrt{q^2-p^3}}&+\sqrt[3]{-q+\sqrt{q^2-p^3}}   \tag*{\textbf{(M1)}}
    \end{align*}
    $$

    Now, substituting back $p=-\dfrac{s}{3}$ and $q=\dfrac{t}{2}$ we obtain

    $$
    \begin{align*}
        &= \sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{t}{2}-\sqrt{\left(\dfrac{t}{2}\right)^2-\left(-\dfrac{s}{3}\right)^3}}+\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{t}{2}+\sqrt{\left(\dfrac{t}{2}\right)^2-\left(-\dfrac{s}{3}\right)^3}} \tag*{\textbf{M1}} \\[12pt]
        &= \sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{t}{2}-\sqrt{\dfrac{t^2}{4}+\dfrac{s^3}{27}}}+\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{t}{2}+\sqrt{\dfrac{t^2}{4}+\dfrac{s^3}{27}}} \tag*{\textbf{A1}}\\[12pt]
        &\hspace{0.275em}\tcbhighmath{= \sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{t}{2}+\sqrt{\dfrac{t^2}{4}+\dfrac{s^3}{27}}}+\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{t}{2}-\sqrt{\dfrac{t^2}{4}+\dfrac{s^3}{27}}}}
    \end{align*}
    $$

  - Using Cardano's formula, with $s=6$ and $t=5$, we get

    $$
    \begin{align*}
        &\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{5}{2}+\sqrt{\dfrac{25}{4}+\dfrac{216}{27}}}+\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{5}{2}-\sqrt{\dfrac{25}{4}+\dfrac{216}{27}}} \tag*{\textbf{M1}}\\[12pt]
        =&\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{5}{2}+\sqrt{\dfrac{57}{4}}}+\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{5}{2}-\sqrt{\dfrac{57}{4}}}\\[12pt]
        &\hspace{-2.9mm}\tcbhighmath{=\sqrt[3]{\dfrac{-5+\sqrt{57}}{2}}+\sqrt[3]{\dfrac{-5-\sqrt{57}}{2}}} \tag*{\textbf{A1}}
    \end{align*}
    $$

  - Substituting $z=x-1$, we get

    $$
    \begin{align*}
        (x-1)^3 + 3 (x-1)^2 - 6 &= 0  \tag*{\textbf{M1}}\\[12pt]
        x^3-3x^2+3x-1+3(x^2-2x+1) - 6 &= 0\\[12pt]
        x^3-3x^2+3x-1+3x^2-6x+3-6 &= 0\\[12pt]
        x^3-3x-4 &= 0 \tag*{\textbf{A1}}\\[-12pt]
    \end{align*}
    $$

    Now, using Cardano's formula, with $s=-3$ and $t=-4$, we obtain

    $$
    \begin{align*}
        x=&\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{-4}{2}+\sqrt{\dfrac{16}{4}+\dfrac{-27}{27}}}+\sqrt[3]{-\dfrac{-4}{2}-\sqrt{\dfrac{16}{4}+\dfrac{-27}{27}}}\\[12pt]
        x=&\sqrt[3]{2+\sqrt{3}}+\sqrt[3]{2-\sqrt{3}}  \tag*{\textbf{A1}}
    \end{align*}
    $$

    Recall, $z=x-1$, therefore, a solution to $z^3+3z^2-6=0$ is

    $$
    \begin{align*}
        &\hspace{-42mm}\tcbhighmath{z=-1+\sqrt[3]{2+\sqrt{3}}+\sqrt[3]{2-\sqrt{3}}} \tag*{\textbf{A1}}
    \end{align*} 
    $$
